{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","content_id":"1bda1bf9-acfe-42b6-8b82-7e7b6417593e","description":"Jonathan Reynolds was appointed Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) on 5 September 2025. He was previously Secretary of State for Business and Trade and President of the Board of Trade from 5 July 2024 to 5 September 2025. He was elected as the MP for Stalybridge and Hyde in May 2010.","details":{"body":"<p>Jonathan Reynolds was appointed Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) on 5 September 2025. He was previously Secretary of State for Business and Trade and President of the Board of Trade from 5 July 2024 to 5 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected as the MP for Stalybridge and Hyde in May 2010.</p>\n","full_name":"Jonathan Reynolds MP","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Jonathan Reynolds MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/66881843ab5fc5929851ba77/s465_jonathan-reynolds.jpg"},"privy_counsellor":true},"document_type":"person","first_published_at":"2024-07-05T16:58:58+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","base_path":"/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","content_id":"1bda1bf9-acfe-42b6-8b82-7e7b6417593e","document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-05T17:05:20Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Jonathan Reynolds MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","withdrawn":false}],"role_appointments":[{"content_id":"0390c3fa-97ba-4e57-9d07-7f9bae896ab0","details":{"current":true,"ended_on":null,"person_appointment_order":3,"started_on":"2025-09-05T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","base_path":"/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","content_id":"1bda1bf9-acfe-42b6-8b82-7e7b6417593e","details":{"body":"<p>Jonathan Reynolds was appointed Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) on 5 September 2025. He was previously Secretary of State for Business and Trade and President of the Board of Trade from 5 July 2024 to 5 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected as the MP for Stalybridge and Hyde in May 2010.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Jonathan Reynolds MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/66881843ab5fc5929851ba77/s465_jonathan-reynolds.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-05T17:05:20Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Jonathan Reynolds MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/jonathan-reynolds","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/parliamentary-secretary-to-the-treasury-and-chief-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/parliamentary-secretary-to-the-treasury-and-chief-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/parliamentary-secretary-to-the-treasury-and-chief-whip","content_id":"845e6a56-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Chief Whip is responsible for administering the whipping system that ensures that members of the party attend and vote in Parliament as the party leadership desires.</p>\n\n<p>Whips are MPs or Lords appointed by each party in Parliament to help organise their party’s contribution to parliamentary business. One of their responsibilities is making sure the maximum number of their party members vote, and vote the way their party wants.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"other-whip-duties\">Other whip duties</h2>\n\n<p>Whips frequently act as tellers (counting votes in divisions). They also manage the pairing system whereby Members of opposing parties both agree not to vote when other business (such as a select committee visit) prevents them from being present at 